urity and poverty alleviation effort. Everyone has an opinion about SNAP, not all of them positive, but its benefits are felt broadly and across party lines. Christopher Bosso makes a clear, nuanced, and impassioned case for protecting this unique food program, exploring its history and breaking down the facts for readers across the political spectrum. Why SNAP Works is an essential book for anyone concerned about food access, poverty, and the “welfare system” in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFood stampsxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPovertyxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520392823?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520392823423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520392823/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles